        "\n",
        "*  For large values of $m$ and under all the assumptions that were made, $~$the $n \\times 1$ vector $\\mathbf{x}_m$ is an approximation to a dominant eigenvector associated with the dominant eigenvalue $\\lambda_1$\n",
